{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866682015,"sessionID":"ses_286193d0effeBJH25U48I4t63R","part":{"id":"prt_d79e710ec001Zhr1JcudBP4HXH","messageID":"msg_d79e6f9c6001hzLJovbdy7njuJ","sessionID":"ses_286193d0effeBJH25U48I4t63R","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-467e14dbef0846aa9518f0ab380138bb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-018: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The Idle Cleanup Controller is responsible for detecting and cleaning up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters in the agentcube system. This controller monitors resource usage and automatically removes resources that have been idle beyond a configurable threshold.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Architecture\n10: \n11: ### Component Structure\n12: \n13: ```\n14: pkg/agentd/\n15: ├── controller/\n16: │   ├── idle_cleanup_controller.go    # Main controller implementation\n17: │   ├── idle_cleanup_controller_test.go\n18: │   └── metrics.go                     # Prometheus metrics\n19: ├── config/\n20: │   └── cleanup_config.go              # Configuration types\n21: └── cleanup/\n22:     ├── detector.go                    # Idle detection logic\n23:     ├── detector_test.go\n24:     ├── cleaner.go                     # Cleanup execution logic\n25:     └── cleaner_test.go\n26: ```\n27: \n28: ### Controller Flow\n29: \n30: ```\n31: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n32: │                    Idle Cleanup Controller                       │\n33: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n34: │                                                                  │\n35: │  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐      │\n36: │  │   Informer   │───▶│   Detector   │───▶│   Cleaner    │      │\n37: │  │  (Watch CRs) │    │ (Check Idle) │    │  (Delete CR) │      │\n38: │  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘      │\n39: │         │                   │                    │              │\n40: │         ▼                   ▼                    ▼              │\n41: │  ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐      │\n42: │  │  Workqueue   │    │   Metrics    │    │   Events     │      │\n43: │  │              │    │              │    │   Recorder   │      │\n44: │  └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘    └──────────────┘      │\n45: │                                                                  │\n46: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Integration with client-go\n50: \n51: The controller uses the generated client-go library for interacting with:\n52: \n53: - `AgentRuntime` CRs via `AgentRuntimeInterface`\n54: - `CodeInterpreter` CRs via `CodeInterpreterInterface`\n55: \n56: ```go\n57: clientset \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go\"\n58: runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## Data Structures\n64: \n65: ### Configuration\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: package config\n69: \n70: type CleanupConfig struct {\n71:     IdleThreshold        time.Duration `json:\"idleThreshold\"`\n72:     CheckInterval        time.Duration `json:\"checkInterval\"`\n73:     MaxConcurrentCleanup int           `json:\"maxConcurrentCleanup\"`\n74:     Namespaces           []string      `json:\"namespaces\"`\n75:     ExcludeLabels        map[string]string `json:\"excludeLabels\"`\n76: }\n77: \n78: type ResourceConfig struct {\n79:     AgentRuntime    ResourceTypeConfig `json:\"agentRuntime\"`\n80:     CodeInterpreter ResourceTypeConfig `json:\"codeInterpreter\"`\n81: }\n82: \n83: type ResourceTypeConfig struct {\n84:     Enabled       bool          `json:\"enabled\"`\n85:     IdleThreshold time.Duration `json:\"idleThreshold\"`\n86:     MaxRetries    int           `json:\"maxRetries\"`\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Idle Detection Result\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: package cleanup\n94: \n95: type IdleState int\n96: \n97: const (\n98:     IdleStateUnknown IdleState = iota\n99:     IdleStateActive\n100:     IdleStateIdle\n101:     IdleStateTerminating\n102: )\n103: \n104: type DetectionResult struct {\n105:     ResourceName      string\n106:     Namespace         string\n107:     ResourceType      string\n108:     State             IdleState\n109:     IdleDuration      time.Duration\n110:     LastActivityTime time.Time\n111:     Reason           string\n112: }\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Cleanup Record\n116: \n117: ```go\n118: type CleanupRecord struct {\n119:     Name         string\n120:     Namespace    string\n121:     ResourceType string\n122:     DeletedAt    time.Time\n123:     Reason       string\n124:     Error        error\n125: }\n126: ```\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## API Contracts\n131: \n132: ### Controller Interface\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: package controller\n136: \n137: type IdleCleanupController interface {\n138:     Run(ctx context.Context, workers int) error\n139:     HasSynced() bool\n140:     Shutdown()\n141: }\n142: \n143: type ControllerOptions struct {\n144:     Client     clientset.Interface\n145:     Config     *config.CleanupConfig\n146:     Recorder   record.EventRecorder\n147:     Metrics    *Metrics\n148: }\n149: ```\n150: \n151: ### Detector Interface\n152: \n153: ```go\n154: package cleanup\n155: \n156: type IdleDetector interface {\n157:     DetectIdle(ctx context.Context, obj runtime.Object) (*DetectionResult, error)\n158:     GetIdleThreshold(resourceType string) time.Duration\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### Cleaner Interface\n163: \n164: ```go\n165: package cleanup\n166: \n167: type ResourceCleaner interface {\n168:     Cleanup(ctx context.Context, result *DetectionResult) (*CleanupRecord, error)\n169:     CleanupBatch(ctx context.Context, results []*DetectionResult) ([]*CleanupRecord, error)\n170: }\n171: ```\n172: \n173: ### Event Types\n174: \n175: ```go\n176: const (\n177:     EventReasonIdleDetected    = \"IdleDetected\"\n178:     EventReasonCleanupStarted  = \"CleanupStarted\"\n179:     EventReasonCleanupSuccess  = \"CleanupSuccess\"\n180:     EventReasonCleanupFailed   = \"CleanupFailed\"\n181: )\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Idle Detection Logic\n187: \n188: ### Detection Criteria\n189: \n190: An AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter is considered idle when:\n191: \n192: 1. **Status.LastActivityTime** is older than the configured threshold\n193: 2. **No active sessions** are registered\n194: 3. **No pending tasks** in the queue\n195: 4. **Resource usage** below minimum threshold (optional)\n196: \n197: ### Detection Implementation\n198: \n199: ```go\n200: func (d *detector) DetectIdle(ctx context.Context, obj runtime.Object) (*DetectionResult, error) {\n201:     switch v := obj.(type) {\n202:     case *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime:\n203:         return d.detectAgentRuntimeIdle(v)\n204:     case *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter:\n205:         return d.detectCodeInterpreterIdle(v)\n206:     default:\n207:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unsupported resource type: %T\", obj)\n208:     }\n209: }\n210: \n211: func (d *detector) detectAgentRuntimeIdle(ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*DetectionResult, error) {\n212:     result := &DetectionResult{\n213:         ResourceName: ar.Name,\n214:         Namespace:    ar.Namespace,\n215:         ResourceType: \"AgentRuntime\",\n216:     }\n217: \n218:     if ar.Status.LastActivityTime == nil {\n219:         result.State = IdleStateUnknown\n220:         result.Reason = \"last activity time not set\"\n221:         return result, nil\n222:     }\n223: \n224:     idleDuration := time.Since(ar.Status.LastActivityTime.Time)\n225:     result.IdleDuration = idleDuration\n226:     result.LastActivityTime = ar.Status.LastActivityTime.Time\n227: \n228:     threshold := d.GetIdleThreshold(\"AgentRuntime\")\n229:     if idleDuration > threshold {\n230:         if ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n231:             result.State = IdleStateTerminating\n232:         } else {\n233:             result.State = IdleStateIdle\n234:             result.Reason = fmt.Sprintf(\"idle for %v (threshold: %v)\", idleDuration, threshold)\n235:         }\n236:     } else {\n237:         result.State = IdleStateActive\n238:     }\n239: \n240:     return result, nil\n241: }\n242: ```\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ## Cleanup Execution\n247: \n248: ### Cleanup Flow\n249: \n250: ```\n251: 1. Validate the resource can be cleaned up\n252: 2. Check for finalizers and handle appropriately\n253: 3. Issue Delete request with grace period\n254: 4. Record cleanup in metrics and events\n255: 5. Handle errors with retry logic\n256: ```\n257: \n258: ### Cleanup Implementation\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: func (c *cleaner) Cleanup(ctx context.Context, result *DetectionResult) (*CleanupRecord, error) {\n262:     record := &CleanupRecord{\n263:         Name:         result.ResourceName,\n264:         Namespace:    result.Namespace,\n265:         ResourceType: result.ResourceType,\n266:     }\n267: \n268:     opts := metav1.DeleteOptions{\n269:         GracePeriodSeconds: ptr.To[int64](30),\n270:     }\n271: \n272:     var err error\n273:     switch result.ResourceType {\n274:     case \"AgentRuntime\":\n275:         err = c.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().\n276:             AgentRuntimes(result.Namespace).\n277:             Delete(ctx, result.ResourceName, opts)\n278:     case \"CodeInterpreter\":\n279:         err = c.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().\n280:             CodeInterpreters(result.Namespace).\n281:             Delete(ctx, result.ResourceName, opts)\n282:     default:\n283:         err = fmt.Errorf(\"unknown resource type: %s\", result.ResourceType)\n284:     }\n285: \n286:     record.DeletedAt = time.Now()\n287:     if err != nil {\n288:         record.Error = err\n289:         record.Reason = fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup failed: %v\", err)\n290:         return record, err\n291:     }\n292: \n293:     record.Reason = result.Reason\n294:     return record, nil\n295: }\n296: ```\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ## Error Handling\n301: \n302: ### Error Categories\n303: \n304: | Category | Description | Action |\n305: |----------|-------------|--------|\n306: | `ErrResourceNotFound` | Resource already deleted | Skip, log as info |\n307: | `ErrConflict` | Concurrent modification | Retry with backoff |\n308: | `ErrForbidden` | Insufficient permissions | Log error, skip |\n309: | `ErrTimeout` | API timeout | Retry with backoff |\n310: | `ErrInternal` | Unexpected error | Log error, increment metric |\n311: \n312: ### Retry Strategy\n313: \n314: ```go\n315: type RetryConfig struct {\n316:     MaxRetries     int\n317:     InitialBackoff time.Duration\n318:     MaxBackoff     time.Duration\n319:     BackoffFactor  float64\n320: }\n321: \n322: func (c *cleaner) cleanupWithRetry(ctx context.Context, result *DetectionResult) (*CleanupRecord, error) {\n323:     var lastErr error\n324:     backoff := c.retryConfig.InitialBackoff\n325: \n326:     for i := 0; i <= c.retryConfig.MaxRetries; i++ {\n327:         record, err := c.Cleanup(ctx, result)\n328:         if err == nil {\n329:             return record, nil\n330:         }\n331: \n332:         if isNonRetryableError(err) {\n333:             return record, err\n334:         }\n335: \n336:         lastErr = err\n337:         select {\n338:         case <-ctx.Done():\n339:             return record, ctx.Err()\n340:         case <-time.After(backoff):\n341:         }\n342: \n343:         backoff = time.Duration(float64(backoff) * c.retryConfig.BackoffFactor)\n344:         if backoff > c.retryConfig.MaxBackoff {\n345:             backoff = c.retryConfig.MaxBackoff\n346:         }\n347:     }\n348: \n349:     return nil, lastErr\n350: }\n351: ```\n352: \n353: ### Event Recording\n354: \n355: ```go\n356: func (c *Controller) recordEvent(obj runtime.Object, eventType, reason, message string) {\n357:     c.recorder.Eventf(obj, eventType, reason, message)\n358: }\n359: ```\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ## Testing Strategy\n364: \n365: ### Unit Tests\n366: \n367: #### Detector Tests\n368: \n369: ```go\n370: func TestDetectAgentRuntimeIdle(t *testing.T) {\n371:     tests := []struct {\n372:         name           string\n373:         ar             *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n374:         threshold      time.Duration\n375:         expectedState  IdleState\n376:         expectError    bool\n377:     }{\n378:         {\n379:             name: \"active runtime\",\n380:             ar: &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n381:                 ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test\"},\n382:                 Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n383:                     LastActivityTime: ptr.To(metav1.Now()),\n384:                 },\n385:             },\n386:             threshold:     5 * time.Minute,\n387:             expectedState: IdleStateActive,\n388:         },\n389:         {\n390:             name: \"idle runtime\",\n391:             ar: &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n392:                 ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test\"},\n393:                 Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n394:                     LastActivityTime: ptr.To(metav1.Time{Time: time.Now().Add(-10 * time.Minute)}),\n395:                 },\n396:             },\n397:             threshold:     5 * time.Minute,\n398:             expectedState: IdleStateIdle,\n399:         },\n400:         {\n401:             name: \"no activity time\",\n402:             ar: &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n403:                 ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{Name: \"test\"},\n404:             },\n405:             threshold:     5 * time.Minute,\n406:             expectedState: IdleStateUnknown,\n407:         },\n408:     }\n409:     // ...\n410: }\n411: ```\n412: \n413: #### Cleaner Tests\n414: \n415: ```go\n416: func TestCleanupResource(t *testing.T) {\n417:     tests := []struct {\n418:         name        string\n419:         result      *DetectionResult\n420:         mockFn      func(mock *mock.MockRuntimeV1alpha1Interface)\n421:         expectError bool\n422:     }{\n423:         {\n424:             name: \"successful cleanup\",\n425:             result: &DetectionResult{\n426:                 ResourceName: \"test\",\n427:                 Namespace:    \"default\",\n428:                 ResourceType: \"AgentRuntime\",\n429:                 State:        IdleStateIdle,\n430:             },\n431:             mockFn: func(m *mock.MockRuntimeV1alpha1Interface) {\n432:                 m.EXPECT().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Return(mockAgentRuntimeClient)\n433:                 mockAgentRuntimeClient.EXPECT().Delete(gomock.Any(), \"test\", gomock.Any()).Return(nil)\n434:             },\n435:         },\n436:         // ...\n437:     }\n438:     // ...\n439: }\n440: ```\n441: \n442: ### Integration Tests\n443: \n444: ```go\n445: func TestControllerIntegration(t *testing.T) {\n446:     ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n447:     defer cancel()\n448: \n449:     fakeClient := fake.NewSimpleClientset()\n450:     ctrl := controller.New(&controller.ControllerOptions{\n451:         Client: fakeClient,\n452:         Config: &config.CleanupConfig{\n453:             IdleThreshold:   1 * time.Minute,\n454:             CheckInterval:   10 * time.Second,\n455:             Namespaces:      []string{\"default\"},\n456:         },\n457:         Recorder: &record.FakeRecorder{},\n458:     })\n459: \n460:     go ctrl.Run(ctx, 2)\n461: \n462:     // Create test resources and verify cleanup\n463:     ar := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n464:         ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n465:             Name: \"test-idle\",\n466:         },\n467:         Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n468:             LastActivityTime: ptr.To(metav1.Time{Time: time.Now().Add(-5 * time.Minute)}),\n469:         },\n470:     }\n471:     _, err := fakeClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n472:     require.NoError(t, err)\n473: \n474:     // Wait and verify cleanup\n475:     assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {\n476:         _, err := fakeClient.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(ctx, \"test-idle\", metav1.GetOptions{})\n477:         return errors.IsNotFound(err)\n478:     }, 5*time.Second, 100*time.Millisecond)\n479: }\n480: ```\n481: \n482: ### Benchmark Tests\n483: \n484: ```go\n485: func BenchmarkDetectIdle(b *testing.B) {\n486:     d := detector.New(5 * time.Minute)\n487:     ar := createTestAgentRuntime()\n488: \n489:     b.ResetTimer()\n490:     for i := 0; i < b.N; i++ {\n491:         d.DetectIdle(context.Background(), ar)\n492:     }\n493: }\n494: ```\n495: \n496: ---\n497: \n498: ## Metrics\n499: \n500: ### Prometheus Metrics\n501: \n502: ```go\n503: var (\n504:     idleResourcesDetected = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n505:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n506:             Name: \"agentcube_idle_cleanup_detected_total\",\n507:             Help: \"Number of idle resources detected\",\n508:         },\n509:         []string{\"resource_type\", \"namespace\"},\n510:     )\n511: \n512:     resourcesCleanedUp = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n513:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n514:             Name: \"agentcube_idle_cleanup_success_total\",\n515:             Help: \"Number of resources successfully cleaned up\",\n516:         },\n517:         []string{\"resource_type\", \"namespace\"},\n518:     )\n519: \n520:     cleanupErrors = prometheus.NewCounterVec(\n521:         prometheus.CounterOpts{\n522:             Name: \"agentcube_idle_cleanup_errors_total\",\n523:             Help: \"Number of cleanup errors\",\n524:         },\n525:         []string{\"resource_type\", \"namespace\", \"error_type\"},\n526:     )\n527: \n528:     detectionLatency = prometheus.NewHistogram(\n529:         prometheus.NewHistogramOpts{\n530:             Name:    \"agentcube_idle_detection_duration_seconds\",\n531:             Help:    \"Time taken to detect idle resources\",\n532:             Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n533:         },\n534:     )\n535: )\n536: ```\n537: \n538: ---\n539: \n540: ## Configuration\n541: \n542: ### Default Configuration\n543: \n544: ```yaml\n545: idleCleanup:\n546:   idleThreshold: 30m\n547:   checkInterval: 5m\n548:   maxConcurrentCleanup: 10\n549:   namespaces:\n550:     - default\n551:   excludeLabels:\n552:     volcano.sh/no-cleanup: \"true\"\n553:   resources:\n554:     agentRuntime:\n555:       enabled: true\n556:       idleThreshold: 30m\n557:       maxRetries: 3\n558:     codeInterpreter:\n559:       enabled: true\n560:       idleThreshold: 15m\n561:       maxRetries: 3\n562: ```\n563: \n564: ### Configuration Loading\n565: \n566: ```go\n567: func LoadConfig(path string) (*CleanupConfig, error) {\n568:     data, err := os.ReadFile(path)\n569:     if err != nil {\n570:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"reading config: %w\", err)\n571:     }\n572: \n573:     var cfg CleanupConfig\n574:     if err := yaml.Unmarshal(data, &cfg); err != nil {\n575:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parsing config: %w\", err)\n576:     }\n577: \n578:     setDefaults(&cfg)\n579:     return &cfg, nil\n580: }\n581: \n582: func setDefaults(cfg *CleanupConfig) {\n583:     if cfg.IdleThreshold == 0 {\n584:         cfg.IdleThreshold = 30 * time.Minute\n585:     }\n586:     if cfg.CheckInterval == 0 {\n587:         cfg.CheckInterval = 5 * time.Minute\n588:     }\n589:     if cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup == 0 {\n590:         cfg.MaxConcurrentCleanup = 10\n591:     }\n592: }\n593: ```\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ## Implementation Checklist\n598: \n599: - [ ] Create `pkg/agentd/controller/idle_cleanup_controller.go`\n600: - [ ] Create `pkg/agentd/controller/metrics.go`\n601: - [ ] Create `pkg/agentd/config/cleanup_config.go`\n602: - [ ] Create `pkg/agentd/cleanup/detector.go`\n603: - [ ] Create `pkg/agentd/cleanup/cleaner.go`\n604: - [ ] Write unit tests for detector\n605: - [ ] Write unit tests for cleaner\n606: - [ ] Write integration tests for controller\n607: - [ ] Add Prometheus metrics registration\n608: - [ ] Create configuration file and loader\n609: - [ ] Add leader election support\n610: - [ ] Document operational runbook\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Dependencies\n615: \n616: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n617: |---------|---------|---------|\n618: | `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client library |\n619: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | API machinery types |\n620: | `k8s.io/code-generator` | v0.34.1 | Code generation |\n621: | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.x | Metrics |\n622: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.x | Controller utilities |\n\n(End of file - total 622 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Idle Cleanup Controller is responsible for detecting and cleaning up idle agent runtimes and code interpreters in the agentcube system. This controller monitors resource usage and automatically removes resources that have been idle beyond a configurable threshold.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/agentd/\n├── controller/\n│   ├── idle_cleanup_controller.go    # Main controller implementation\n│   ├── idle_cleanup_controller_test.go\n│   └── metrics.go                     # Prometheus metrics\n├── config/\n│   └── cleanup_config.go              # Configuration types","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775866681914,"end":1775866682011}}}}
