{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775866834070,"sessionID":"ses_286193d0effeBJH25U48I4t63R","part":{"id":"prt_d79e96c2b001wXn2fDTWT92aZF","messageID":"msg_d79e79ff300158FOLC2OffkSem","sessionID":"ses_286193d0effeBJH25U48I4t63R","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-ae4addaf83b44c67b0174136a0dbaeb9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-019 — CLI 二进制入口 (4 binaries)\n\n**Module:** `cmd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nImplement CLI binary entry points for four core AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Agentd, Router, and picod. Each binary provides a `main.go` entry point that initializes logging, parses command-line flags, constructs configuration, and launches the respective server/controller.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: workloadmanager binary entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Workload Manager server at `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`.\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager imports\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading imports\n- **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n  - `context` for server lifecycle\n  - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n  - `os` for exit handling\n  - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` for server implementation\n  - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager flag definitions\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n- **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n  - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n  - `kubeconfig` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Kubeconfig path (empty for in-cluster)\"`)\n  - `namespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Namespace to watch (empty for all)\"`)\n  - `redisAddr` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis address\"`)\n  - `redisPassword` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis password\"`)\n  - `sshUsername` (`string`, default `\"sandbox\"`, description `\"SSH username for sandbox access\"`)\n  - `sshPort` (`int`, default `22`, description `\"SSH port for sandbox access\"`)\n  - `runtimeClassName` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Runtime class name for pods\"`)\n  - `metricsPort` (`int`, default `8081`, description `\"Metrics port\"`)\n  - `enableLeaderElection` (`bool`, default `false`, description `\"Enable leader election\"`)\n  - `leaderElectionNamespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Leader election namespace\"`)\n  - `leaderElectionID` (`string`, default `\"workloadmanager\"`, description `\"Leader election ID\"`)\n  - `syncPeriod` (`duration`, default `30s`, description `\"Sync period for informers\"`)\n  - `concurrentReconciles` (`int`, default `5`, description `\"Concurrent reconcile workers\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager klog initialization\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n- **WHEN** `main()` starts\n- **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n- AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager flag parsing\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n- **WHEN** `flag.Parse()` is called\n- **THEN** all defined flags SHALL be parsed and available\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager config construction\n- **GIVEN** parsed flags\n- **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n- **THEN** `pkg/workloadmanager.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n  - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n  - `Kubeconfig`: from `--kubeconfig` flag\n  - `Namespace`: from `--namespace` flag (or in-cluster namespace via fieldRef if empty)\n  - `RedisAddr`: from `--redisAddr` flag (or env `REDIS_ADDR`)\n  - `RedisPassword`: from `--redisPassword` flag (or env `REDIS_PASSWORD`)\n  - `SSHUsername`: from `--sshUsername` flag\n  - `SSHPort`: from `--sshPort` flag\n  - `RuntimeClassName`: from `--runtimeClassName` flag\n  - `MetricsPort`: from `--metricsPort` flag\n  - `EnableLeaderElection`: from `--enableLeaderElection` flag\n  - `LeaderElectionNamespace`: from `--leaderElectionNamespace` flag\n  - `LeaderElectionID`: from `--leaderElectionID` flag\n  - `SyncPeriod`: from `--syncPeriod` flag\n  - `ConcurrentReconciles`: from `--concurrentReconciles` flag\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager server creation\n- **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n- **WHEN** calling `pkg/workloadmanager.NewServer(config)`\n- **THEN** server instance SHALL be created\n- AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager server run\n- **GIVEN** successful server creation\n- **WHEN** calling `server.Run(context.Background())`\n- **THEN** server SHALL start and block until termination\n- AND if run fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager graceful shutdown\n- **GIVEN** `server.Run` receives SIGTERM/SIGINT\n- **WHEN** context is cancelled\n- **THEN** server SHALL gracefully shut down\n- AND all controllers SHALL stop reconciling\n- AND `klog.Info(\"shutting down workload manager\")` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: agentd binary entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Agent Daemon at `cmd/agentd/main.go`.\n\n#### Scenario: agentd imports\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading imports\n- **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n  - `context` for server lifecycle\n  - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n  - `os` for exit handling\n  - `os/signal` for signal handling\n  - `syscall` for signal types\n  - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd` for agent daemon implementation\n  - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: agentd flag definitions\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n- **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n  - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n  - `workspace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Workspace directory path\"`)\n  - `kubeconfig` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Kubeconfig path\"`)\n  - `namespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Namespace for agent sandbox\"`)\n  - `redisAddr` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis address\"`)\n  - `redisPassword` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis password\"`)\n  - `routerURL` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Router URL for session routing\"`)\n  - `workloadManagerURL` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Workload Manager URL\"`)\n  - `idleTimeout` (`duration`, default `15m`, description `\"Idle timeout for sessions\"`)\n  - `maxSessionDuration` (`duration`, default `8h`, description `\"Maximum session duration\"`)\n  - `verbose` (`bool`, default `false`, description `\"Enable verbose logging\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: agentd klog initialization\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n- **WHEN** `main()` starts\n- **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n- AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: agentd config construction\n- **GIVEN** parsed flags\n- **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n- **THEN** `pkg/agentd.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n  - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n  - `Workspace`: from `--workspace` flag (current directory if empty)\n  - `Kubeconfig`: from `--kubeconfig` flag\n  - `Namespace`: from `--namespace` flag\n  - `RedisAddr`: from `--redisAddr` flag (or env `REDIS_ADDR`)\n  - `RedisPassword`: from `--redisPassword` flag (or env `REDIS_PASSWORD`)\n  - `RouterURL`: from `--routerURL` flag\n  - `WorkloadManagerURL`: from `--workloadManagerURL` flag\n  - `IdleTimeout`: from `--idleTimeout` flag\n  - `MaxSessionDuration`: from `--maxSessionDuration` flag\n  - `Verbose`: from `--verbose` flag\n\n#### Scenario: agentd daemon creation\n- **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n- **WHEN** calling `pkg/agentd.NewDaemon(config)`\n- **THEN** daemon instance SHALL be created\n- AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create agentd: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: agentd daemon run\n- **GIVEN** successful daemon creation\n- **WHEN** calling `daemon.Run(ctx)`\n- **THEN** daemon SHALL start HTTP server and background controllers\n- AND signal handler SHALL wait for SIGTERM/SIGINT\n\n#### Scenario: agentd signal handling\n- **GIVEN** running daemon\n- **WHEN** SIGTERM or SIGINT is received\n- **THEN** context SHALL be cancelled\n- AND `klog.Info(\"received shutdown signal\")` SHALL be called\n- AND daemon SHALL stop gracefully\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: router binary entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for the Router at `cmd/router/main.go`.\n\n#### Scenario: router imports\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading imports\n- **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n  - `context` for server lifecycle\n  - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n  - `os` for exit handling\n  - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` for router implementation\n  - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: router flag definitions\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n- **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n  - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n  - `debug` (`bool`, default `false`, description `\"Enable debug mode\"`)\n  - `redisAddr` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis address\"`)\n  - `redisPassword` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Redis password\"`)\n  - `workloadManagerURL` (`string`, default `\"http://workloadmanager:8080\"`, description `\"Workload Manager URL\"`)\n  - `namespace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Namespace to operate in\"`)\n  - `metricsPort` (`int`, default `8081`, description `\"Metrics port\"`)\n  - `sessionTimeout` (`duration`, default `15m`, description `\"Session timeout\"`)\n  - `maxSessionDuration` (`duration`, default `8h`, description `\"Maximum session duration\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: router klog initialization\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main.go`\n- **WHEN** `main()` starts\n- **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n- AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: router config construction\n- **GIVEN** parsed flags\n- **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n- **THEN** `pkg/router.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n  - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n  - `Debug`: from `--debug` flag\n  - `RedisAddr`: from `--redisAddr` flag (or env `REDIS_ADDR`)\n  - `RedisPassword`: from `--redisPassword` flag (or env `REDIS_PASSWORD`)\n  - `WorkloadManagerURL`: from `--workloadManagerURL` flag (or env `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL`)\n  - `Namespace`: from `--namespace` flag (or env `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`)\n  - `MetricsPort`: from `--metricsPort` flag\n  - `SessionTimeout`: from `--sessionTimeout` flag\n  - `MaxSessionDuration`: from `--maxSessionDuration` flag\n\n#### Scenario: router server creation\n- **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n- **WHEN** calling `pkg/router.NewServer(config)`\n- **THEN** router server SHALL be created\n- AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create router: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: router server run\n- **GIVEN** successful router creation\n- **WHEN** calling `server.Run(context.Background())`\n- **THEN** router SHALL start HTTP server\n- AND if run fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"router error: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: router debug mode logging\n- **GIVEN** `--debug` flag is `true`\n- **WHEN** router starts\n- **THEN** `klog.SetLogger(klog.NewKlogr())` MAY be called with verbose settings\n- AND debug-level logs SHALL be emitted\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: picod binary entry point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a CLI entry point for picod (code interpreter daemon) at `cmd/picod/main.go`.\n\n#### Scenario: picod imports\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading imports\n- **THEN** imports SHALL include:\n  - `context` for server lifecycle\n  - `flag` for CLI flag parsing\n  - `os` for exit handling\n  - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` for picod server implementation\n  - `k8s.io/klog/v2` for structured logging\n\n#### Scenario: picod flag definitions\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n- **WHEN** reading flag definitions\n- **THEN** flags SHALL be defined:\n  - `port` (`int`, default `8080`, description `\"HTTP listening port\"`)\n  - `workspace` (`string`, default `\"\"`, description `\"Workspace directory path (empty means current directory)\"`)\n\n#### Scenario: picod klog initialization\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main.go`\n- **WHEN** `main()` starts\n- **THEN** `klog.InitFlags(nil)` SHALL be called\n- AND `flag.Set(\"logtostderr\", \"true\")` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: picod config construction\n- **GIVEN** parsed flags\n- **WHEN** constructing `Config`\n- **THEN** `pkg/picod.Config` SHALL be populated with:\n  - `Port`: from `--port` flag\n  - `Workspace`: from `--workspace` flag\n\n#### Scenario: picod server creation\n- **GIVEN** populated `Config`\n- **WHEN** calling `pkg/picod.NewServer(config)`\n- **THEN** picod server SHALL be created\n- AND if creation fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"failed to create server: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: picod server run\n- **GIVEN** successful server creation\n- **WHEN** calling `server.Run(context.Background())`\n- **THEN** picod SHALL start HTTP server for code execution\n- AND if run fails, `klog.Fatalf(\"server error: %v\", err)` SHALL be called\n- AND `os.Exit(1)` SHALL be called\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: flag naming conventions\n\nThe system SHALL follow consistent flag naming conventions for all binaries.\n\n#### Scenario: flag naming style\n- **GIVEN** any CLI binary in `cmd/`\n- **WHEN** defining flags\n- **THEN** flags SHALL use:\n  - lowercase names without underscores (e.g., `kubeconfig`, not `kube_config`)\n  - descriptive help text\n  - sensible defaults matching production requirements\n\n#### Scenario: flag default behavior\n- **GIVEN** flags with empty string defaults\n- **WHEN** flag is not provided\n- **THEN** code SHALL check for environment variable fallback where applicable\n- AND environment variables SHALL use uppercase underscore naming (e.g., `REDIS_ADDR`)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: environment variable integration\n\nThe system SHALL support environment variable fallback for key configuration options.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis configuration from environment\n- **GIVEN** `--redisAddr` and `--redisPassword` flags are empty\n- **WHEN** binary starts\n- **THEN** `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` environment variables SHALL be read\n- AND values SHALL populate the respective Config fields\n\n#### Scenario: Workload Manager URL from environment\n- **GIVEN** router binary with empty `--workloadManagerURL`\n- **WHEN** router starts\n- **THEN** `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable SHALL be read\n- AND value SHALL populate Config.WorkloadManagerURL\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace from environment\n- **GIVEN** binaries with empty `--namespace`\n- **WHEN** running in-cluster\n- **THEN** `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` environment variable SHALL be read\n- AND if not set, downward API fieldRef may be used for namespace detection\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: exit codes\n\nThe system SHALL use consistent exit codes across all binaries.\n\n#### Scenario: successful execution\n- **GIVEN** binary runs and completes\n- **WHEN** no error occurs\n- **THEN** process SHALL exit with code `0`\n\n#### Scenario: initialization failure\n- **GIVEN** binary fails to initialize\n- **WHEN** `NewServer` or `NewDaemon` returns error\n- **THEN** process SHALL exit with code `1`\n- AND error SHALL be logged via `klog.Fatalf`\n\n#### Scenario: runtime failure\n- **GIVEN** binary fails during execution\n- **WHEN** `Run` returns error\n- **THEN** process SHALL exit with code `1`\n- AND error SHALL be logged via `klog.Fatalf`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Makefile build integration\n\nThe system SHALL integrate with Makefile targets for building binaries.\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager build target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** running `make build`\n- **THEN** `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` SHALL be executed\n- AND binary SHALL be placed at `bin/workloadmanager`\n\n#### Scenario: agentd build target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** running `make build-agentd`\n- **THEN** `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` SHALL be executed\n- AND binary SHALL be placed at `bin/agentd`\n\n#### Scenario: router build target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** running `make build-router`\n- **THEN** `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` SHALL be executed\n- AND binary SHALL be placed at `bin/agentcube-router`\n\n#### Scenario: build all target\n- **GIVEN** `Makefile`\n- **WHEN** running `make build-all`\n- **THEN** all three binaries SHALL be built (workloadmanager, agentd, agentcube-router)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Dockerfile integration\n\nThe system SHALL provide Dockerfiles for containerizing binaries.\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile`\n- **WHEN** building image\n- **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL compile `./cmd/workload-manager` as `workloadmanager`\n- AND runtime SHALL use Alpine 3.19 with user `apiserver` UID 1000\n- AND port 8080 SHALL be exposed\n\n#### Scenario: router Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n- **WHEN** building image\n- **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL compile `./cmd/router` as `agentcube-router`\n- AND runtime SHALL use Alpine 3.19 with user `router` UID 1000\n- AND port 8080 SHALL be exposed\n\n#### Scenario: picod Dockerfile\n- **GIVEN** `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n- **WHEN** building image\n- **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL compile `./cmd/picod` as `picod`\n- AND runtime SHALL use Ubuntu 24.04 with Python3 installed\n- AND binary SHALL run as root for sandbox permissions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Package structure\n\nThe system SHALL organize cmd files correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: workloadmanager main.go location\n- **GIVEN** repository root\n- **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n- **THEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: agentd main.go location\n- **GIVEN** repository root\n- **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n- **THEN** `cmd/agentd/main.go` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: router main.go location\n- **GIVEN** repository root\n- **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n- **THEN** `cmd/router/main.go` SHALL exist\n\n#### Scenario: picod main.go location\n- **GIVEN** repository root\n- **WHEN** listing `cmd/`\n- **THEN** `cmd/picod/main.go` SHALL exist\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for binary entry points\n\nThe system SHALL have unit tests verifying flag parsing and config construction.\n\n#### Scenario: TestWorkloadManagerFlagParsing\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/workload-manager/main_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Default flag values are correct\n  - Custom flag values override defaults\n  - Config construction maps flags correctly\n\n#### Scenario: TestRouterFlagParsing\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/router/main_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Default flag values are correct\n  - Debug mode flag is parsed\n  - WorkloadManagerURL can be overridden\n\n#### Scenario: TestAgentdFlagParsing\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/agentd/main_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Default idle timeout is 15 minutes\n  - Default max session duration is 8 hours\n  - Workspace flag handling\n\n#### Scenario: TestPicodFlagParsing\n- **GIVEN** `cmd/picod/main_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Default port is 8080\n  - Workspace flag handling with empty default\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| DefaultPort | `8080` | all binaries | Default HTTP listening port |\n| DefaultMetricsPort | `8081` | workloadmanager, router | Default metrics port |\n| DefaultIdleTimeout | `15m` | agentd | Default idle session timeout |\n| DefaultMaxSessionDuration | `8h` | agentd, router | Default maximum session duration |\n| DefaultSSHUsername | `\"sandbox\"` | workloadmanager | Default SSH username |\n| DefaultSSHPort | `22` | workloadmanager | Default SSH port |\n| DefaultSyncPeriod | `30s` | workloadmanager | Default informer sync period |\n| DefaultConcurrentReconciles | `5` | workloadmanager | Default reconcile worker count |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager` | Internal | Workload Manager server implementation |\n| `pkg/agentd` | Internal | Agent Daemon implementation |\n| `pkg/router` | Internal | Router server implementation |\n| `pkg/picod` | Internal | picod server implementation |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.x | Structured logging |\n| `flag` | Standard | CLI flag parsing |\n| `context` | Standard | Server lifecycle management |\n| `os` | Standard | Exit handling |\n| `os/signal` | Standard | Signal handling (agentd) |\n| `syscall` | Standard | Signal types (agentd) |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Create | Workload Manager binary entry point with flags for port, kubeconfig, redis, SSH, leader election, etc. |\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Create | Agent Daemon binary entry point with flags for port, workspace, redis, router URL, idle timeout |\n| `cmd/agentd/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n| `cmd/router/main.go` | Create | Router binary entry point with flags for port, debug, redis, workload manager URL |\n| `cmd/router/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n| `cmd/picod/main.go` | Create | picod binary entry point with flags for port, workspace |\n| `cmd/picod/main_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for flag parsing and config construction |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `changes/AR-007/delta-spec.md` — Workload Manager controller implementation\n- `changes/AR-018/delta-spec.md` — Agentd idle cleanup controller\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for CR operations\n- `deployment/design.md` — Dockerfile patterns and Makefile targets\n- `cli-toolkit/design.md` — Python CLI (kubectl-agentcube) reference\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] workloadmanager main.go imports klog, flag, context, os\n- [ ] workloadmanager flags: port, kubeconfig, namespace, redisAddr, redisPassword, SSH params, leader election, sync period\n- [ ] workloadmanager calls NewServer(config) and Run(ctx)\n- [ ] agentd main.go imports signal/syscall for graceful shutdown\n- [ ] agentd flags: port, workspace, kubeconfig, redis, routerURL, workloadManagerURL, idleTimeout\n- [ ] agentd calls NewDaemon(config) and Run(ctx)\n- [ ] router main.go flags: port, debug, redisAddr, workloadManagerURL\n- [ ] router calls NewServer(config) and Run(ctx)\n- [ ] picod main.go flags: port, workspace (minimal)\n- [ ] picod calls NewServer(config) and Run(ctx)\n- [ ] Environment variable fallback for redisAddr, redisPassword, workloadManagerURL, namespace\n- [ ] Exit codes: 0 for success, 1 for failure\n- [ ] klog.InitFlags(nil) and logtostderr=true in all binaries\n- [ ] Makefile targets: build, build-agentd, build-router, build-all\n- [ ] Dockerfiles reference correct cmd paths\n- [ ] Package structure: cmd/workload-manager/, cmd/agentd/, cmd/router/, cmd/picod/\n- [ ] Unit tests for flag parsing in each binary\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/cmd/picod/main.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-019/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775866834058,"end":1775866834067}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775866834095,"sessionID":"ses_286193d0effeBJH25U48I4t63R","part":{"id":"prt_d79e96c95001kwDb77cjDqouB9","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79e79ff300158FOLC2OffkSem","sessionID":"ses_286193d0effeBJH25U48I4t63R","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":61011,"input":414,"output":6006,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":54591}},"cost":0}}
